            "comments": [
                {
                    "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/13225779/comment/16835375",
                    "id": "16835375",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=jorisvandenbossche",
                        "name": "jorisvandenbossche",
                        "key": "jorisvandenbossche",
                        "avatarUrls": {
                            "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452",
                            "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452",
                            "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452",
                            "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"
                        },
                        "displayName": "Joris Van den Bossche",
                        "active": true,
                        "timeZone": "Europe/Brussels"
                    },
                    "body": "[~fjetter] thanks for the report!\r\n\r\nThe problem here is that the {{non_empty}} and {{empty}} dataframes have a different index (due to the {{drop}} call):\r\n\r\n{code}\r\n>>> non_empty.index\r\nRangeIndex(start=0, stop=1, step=1)\r\n\r\n>>> empty.index\r\nInt64Index([], dtype='int64')\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nAnd it is the type of Index that pyarrow uses to decide whether to serialize the index into an actual column or in metadata only (in case of a RangeIndex). \r\nSo it is doing the \"correct\" thing here, although of course surprising / unexpected (but which is also due to that it is not always clear in pandas when you have a RangeIndex and when not)\r\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=jorisvandenbossche",
                        "name": "jorisvandenbossche",
                        "key": "jorisvandenbossche",
                        "avatarUrls": {
                            "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452",
                            "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452",
