                        "displayName": "Joris Van den Bossche",
                        "active": true,
                        "timeZone": "Europe/Brussels"
                    },
                    "body": "Yeah, I don't think there is anything we can do from our side (we don't want to special case empty Int64 index I think).\r\n\r\nWith the new {{preserve_index=True}} you can ensure to _always_ have the index as a column, but for the other way around (ensure it is always serialized as metadata), the user needs to ensure the index is actually a RangeIndex.\r\n\r\n\u00a0\r\n\r\nSo [~fjetter] if you have other ideas how to deal with this, that's very welcome, but for now closing this issue.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=jorisvandenbossche",
                        "name": "jorisvandenbossche",
                        "key": "jorisvandenbossche",
